FT  21 MAR 92 / Finance &amp; The Family (Briefcase): Tax relief on study
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I AM taking a part time evening course at the local College of Further
Education. The course is the BTEC National Certificate in Business and
Finance. The fees this year are Pounds 180 and textbooks cost Pounds 40. I
fund this myself. Is it possible to claim tax allowances for these
expenditures from the Inland Revenue?
No; the tax relief for certain expenditure on vocational training (announced
in last year's Budget) does not apply to payments made before the beginning
of 1992-93.
