FT  20 MAR 92 / The Lex Column: Waste Management
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pathfinder prospectus for the flotation of Waste Management
International confirms that its US parent has posed a teaser for UK
investors. Assuming WMI increases its earnings per share by one third this
year, its shares will be on a prospective multiple of 23 if priced in the
middle of the range suggested by the group's advisers, or 26 at the top of
the range. That compares with historic multiples of 19 for Caird after
yesterday's results, and 18 for Shanks &amp; McEwan. It is just possible that
both valuations are right. The flotation could prove a lively affair all the
same.
