FT  20 MAR 92 / Election 1992: Hurd's maths - Ballot Box
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Douglas Hurd may be a very professional foreign secretary, but should be
kept away from anything to do with statistics.
He told an election meeting in Southampton on Wednesday that the reason why
the proportion of tax paid by the country's top 5 per cent of salary earners
had risen during the government's lifetime was that there are more of them.
When an FT correspondent gently pointed out to him that 5 per cent is 5 per
cent is 5 per cent, the foreign secretary replied diplomatically that he had
'elided' two separate arguments.
