FT  20 MAR 92 / World Commodities Prices: Fruit &amp; Vegetables
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Early forced rhubarb at 45-60p a lb (40-65p) is superb this week, reports
FFVIB. Grapes remain a superb choice with Cape seedless at 90p-Pounds 1.20 a
lb (90p-Pounds 1.20). Jaffa oranges at 12-30p each (12-30p) and Spania
strawberries at 65-80p a  1/2 lb (85p-Pounds 1.00) are also good value for
money. An excellent vegetable buy is French cauliflower at 50-75p each
(60-80p), also good is broccoli at 40-48p a 1/2 lb (35-45p), Spring cabbage
at 25-35p a lb (25-35p) and parsnips at 30-40p a lb (30-40p). The new crop
of English watercress is now available at 35-45p a bunch (35-45p), together
with radishes at 30-45p a bunch (30-45p).
