issue. The shares will be priced at the beginning of April.
Taiwan's central bank said earlier this year that it would restrict the flow
of equity investment funds into the island, much to the annoyance of Taiwan
fund managers. The central bank has delayed the approval of remittances of
funds by foreign firms investing in Taiwanese stocks because of concern
about the appreciation of the Taiwan dollar against the US dollar.
