FT  20 MAR 92 / Observer: Speechless
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An unexpected visitor turns up in heaven. St Peter asks for some
identification. The new arrival is a little taken aback, and insists that he
is who he says he is. St Peter is still not sure.
Suddenly, the new arrival spots someone he knows. 'I'm sure that's Mrs
Thatcher over there - she'll be able to vouchsafe for me.'
Non-plussed, St Peter replies: 'That's not Mrs Thatcher, that's God.'
