FT  20 MAR 92 / Observer: Yellow peril
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There were worried frowns recently at Thompson Clive Investments, a
specialist venture capital investment trust, when a look through its stock
exchange yellow book revealed that it was supposed to notify the market
about 'any change in the directorate'. So it rushed in a letter about one
Stephen Black who resigned last June.
Imagine the surprise of the company secretary yesterday when Observer told
her that the announcement was running on Topic, the stock exchange
information service. 'They shouldn't have done that,' said she - obviously
still less than an expert on the ways of the market.
'We were only floated in September 1988, and we're still on the learning
curve,' explains director Charles Fitzherbert.
Hardly an encouraging message for his shareholders.
